Left brachial access was obtained under ultrasound guidance and a 5-F pigtail catheter was sited in the infrarenal aorta. The angiogram showed a patent sac and filling of the 2 large lumbar arteries (Figure 2
). The pigtail was exchanged for a long 5-F sheath and the lumbar vessels were embolized with coils and a 10 mm AVP (AGA Medical, Golden Valley, Minnesota) was placed into the ligation zone. Post placement angiogram demonstrated an occluded sac (Figure 3
). Follow-up CT scan at 3 months after the embolization confirmed sac occlusion (Figure 4
) and concomitant reduction in sac size from 5.9 to 5.4 cm.
